Grade 5 learners reopened for the third term on January 3, alongside other learners across the country. Their national assessment, which will account for 20 per cent of overall score, is scheduled for January 31. The learners will proceed on 7 weeks holiday on March 4, together with other learners and resume learning on April 25 as grade six learners. Final assessment, which accounts for 40, will be held between November 28 and December 1.